Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getMultiCpuUsage(25.10)                                getMultiCpuUsage(25.10)

Name
       getMultiCpuUsage - Displays the requested number of threads or hosts

Syntax
       getMultiCpuUsage

       [-help]

       [-autoPageFaultMonitor]

       [-cpuPerRemoteHost]

       [-keepLicense]

       [-localCpu]

       [-remoteHost]

       [-threadInfo]

       [-verbose]

       Displays the requested number of threads or hosts.

       To request threads or hosts, use setMultiCpuUsage.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs the command usage and a brief description about the com-
              mand parameters.

       -autoPageFaultMonitor
              Displays  the  warning rank set for performance issues caused by
              major page faults

       -cpuPerRemoteHost
              Displays the number of CPUs available on every remote  host  for
              Superthreading.

       -keepLicense
              Displays  the  current setting for the setMultiCpuUsage -keepLi-
              cense parameter.

       -localCpu
              Displays the number of available local CPUs for multi-threading.

       -remoteHost
              Displays the number of available remote  hosts  for  distributed
              processing or Superthreading.

       -threadInfo
              Displays the level of informational messages for each thread.

       -verbose
              Displays a message with the current multiple-CPU setting.

Examples
              * The following command displays the requested number of threads
                for multi-threading:

                getMultiCpuUsage -localCpu

              * The  following command displays the requested number of remote
                hosts for Superthreading or distributed processing:

                getMultiCpuUsage -remoteHost

              * The following command displays the requested  number  of  CPUs
                per remote hosts for Superthreading:

                getMultiCpuUsage -cpuPerRemoteHost

Related Information
